  "body": "# Proposal: Support to use (part of) CSS units in Weex DSL\r\n\r\n## Background\r\n\r\nIn the current version, weex ignored all CSS units, they are all treated as relative values.\r\nIn order to better support the configurable viewport ( #421 ), we should also introduce some CSS units, especially the absolute length of the unit.\r\n\r\n## Purpose\r\n\r\n+ Follow up the CSS standard specification.\r\n+ Write non-responsive layouts. ( #965 #1543 )\r\n+ Write device based layouts. ( #27 #491 #1022 )\r\n\r\n## Introduction\r\n\r\nSupport to use `pt` (or `dp`) as absolute units in Weex DSL.\r\n\r\n+ `pt`, the absolute units used in CSS and iOS.\r\n+ `dp`, the absolute unit used in Android.\r\n\r\nI personally think it's more appropriate to use `pt`, because CSS already has this attribute, doing so reduces the learning costs of users and avoids introducing our own concepts.\r\n\r\n### Renderer\r\n\r\nNo need to change.\r\n\r\nRenderers are only need to be confirmed what's the meaning of deviceWidth: `deviceWidth` should be the device pixel width (currently is the screen resolution width, if there has a difference between them, native should also provide a new environment parameter) .\r\n\r\n### JS Runtime\r\n\r\nNo need to change.\r\n\r\n### JS Framework\r\n\r\nThe js framework handles the unit of the style attribute, and if it encounters a string ending with `pt` in the style value, it should be converted to a number relative to the width of the screen by calculation.\r\n\r\n```\r\nrealWidth = number * viewportWidth / deviceWidth\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut it would be a little harmful for the performance.\r\n\r\n### transformer\r\n\r\nTransformer should retain the `pt` units, and still ignore the other units (as `px`) to be compatible with the old version.\r\n\r\nBefore:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.box {\r\n  width: 600px;\r\n  height: 200pt;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAfter:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nmodule.exports.style = {\r\n  \"box\": {\r\n    \"width\": 600,\r\n    \"height\": \"200pt\"\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Tools\r\n\r\nNo need to change.\r\n\r\n### User Experience\r\n\r\nDevelopers have more flexibility in writing styles.\r\n\r\nDraw a box with one-pixel width border:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.box {\r\n   width: 500;\r\n   height: 300;\r\n   border-width: 1pt;\r\n   border-color: #666666;\r\n   border-style: solid;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nDraw a box with fixed width and height:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.box {\r\n   width: 640pt;\r\n   height: 300pt;\r\n   margin: auto;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
